summary: This is a Federal Bureau of Prisons prisoner remand form, used to document the arrest and initial processing of an individual into custody. The form is partially filled out but contains no specific data about the prisoner's identity, charges, or arresting details.
keyFacts: The document is a standard Bureau of Prisons form (BP-5377.058) for remanding a prisoner to a Metropolitan Correctional Center (MCC) or Metropolitan Detention Center (MDC).
All specific data fields on the form (Name, AKAs, Charges, Date of Arrest, etc.) are blank or contain only placeholder text.
The form does not identify any individual, making it impossible to determine if it relates directly to Jeffrey Epstein or another case figure.
The form's reference number (EFTA00120669) suggests it is part of a larger document set related to the Epstein case, but this specific page contains no substantive information.
